<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4639973>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 2: Scheloribates elegans Hammer, 1958: A – body dorsally; B – body ventrally (gnathosoma and legs not illustrated); C – prodorsum and anterior part of notogaster laterally (gnathosoma and legs not illustrated); D – rostral seta; E – medio-distal part of sensillus; F – pedotectum II, discidium and epimeral setae 3c, 4c in dissected specimen; G – left genital plate and epimaral seta 3a; H – left anal plate and adanal setae ad1-ad3; I – claws on leg I. Scale bars (A-C) 200 µm, scale bar (D, I) 10 µm, scale bar (E-H) 20 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4639973/files/figure.png" .

